Data Types in Java
     --> 1. Primitive Data Type
                (i) int : stores integer
                (ii) byte : stores number, from -127 to 128
                (iii) long : stores larger integer
                (iv) float : stores decimal value
                (v) double : stores larger decimal value
                (vi) char : stores character
                (vii) short : stores smaller integer value
                (viii) bool : True/False

     --> 2. Non Primitive Data Type
                Non primitive data types are derive d from primitive data types.